The paper deals with texture recognition and remote sensing scene classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Local Binary Patterns (LBP) for encoding texture information, which falls under the category of image processing (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper explores different deep network fusion architectures, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
